// Man page for heist
manHeist="HEIST(1)                         X Shell Manual                         HEIST(1)

<b>NAME</b>
    heist - Interactive bank heist loop
<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>heist</b>
<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    Interactive heist helper. Acquires a root shell on your bank once,
    then repeatedly prompts for target banks. After each successful
    target, wait for your manual transfer and corrupt both
    /server/transactions.log files. Enter <b>!</b> to cancel/quit.
<b>FLOW</b>
    1. Prompt for your bank (ip|domain) and port (default 141)
    2. Exploit and require root; re-prompt on failure
    3. Prompt for target bank and port
    4. Exploit and require root; re-prompt on failure
    5. Press enter after the transfer; corrupt both logs
    6. Prompt for the next target (your bank is kept)
    7. Repeat until <b>!</b>
<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <b>heist</b>
    Start the interactive heist loop

    At prompts, enter <b>!</b> to cancel (same as other Gui inputs)"
